sentence: Sydney Goldstein, who also wrote the Royal Society memoir for Kármán, reviewed the autobiography Sydney Goldstein (1968) Journal of Fluid Mechanics 33 (2) and remembered an eminent engineer and scientist, warm-hearted and witty, much traveled, well-known by many, devoted to international collaboration, who, in his own words, as a scientist found the military ' the most comfortable group to deal with '.
